metadata.name: Perpetual line #112
metadata.description:
Artwork.
Steeped in abstraction and minimalism, this collection produces a stratification of colours and rythms by applying a set of geometric rules.

When the shimmer of the work comes to life, the very principle of kinetic art is revealed in all its ethereal finesse.
The lines, in perpetual movement, generate a subtle moiré effect, reminiscent of the magic of the aurora borealis.
Their simultaneous and contrasting shades of blue and red intersect relentlessly in an hypnotic movement,
perfectly balanced. If interaction is desired, they animate at another rhythm.
A majestic calm emanates from this cybernetic creation, seemingly coming from an outer world,
provoking an hypnotic and soothing fascination that is truly amazing.

the algorithm draws two surfaces of lines that cross to develop a moiré of colors.
Shortcuts: [+][-] increase de speed, [click] Morf, [p] Print png.

metadata.name: Color Fields 2022, Vol.1 #20
metadata.description:
Color Fields 2022, Vol.1

A digital re-interpretation of 1960's color field paitings.

A mix of P5 noise, lerpColor and blendMode.

Pressing 's' saves the image as a PNG file.

This Generative Token creates two color field bars in a vertical alignment and draws them beside each other. The difference in color, shades, tones is realized using noise fields, the lerpColor function to blend two colors into one another, and the canvas blendMode, which affects how pixel are finally blended on-screen.

At startup, the sketch randomly selects four colors from the hue color model. Hue, saturation and brightness are chosen so that each color is not "too close" to one another, depending on predefined bands.

Then it creates four noise fields from the size of one of the two bars.

A bar is produced via these steps:
- Run the following for each pixel:
- Take the first two colors from above and use lerpColor to blend between them.
- The interpolation amount for lerpColor is taken from the 1st noise field.
- Add brightness to the resulting color as value from the 2nd noise field.
- Paint this pixel.
- Paint the ragged border lines by subdividing a line into many small segments, adding coordinate jitter and paint over several times using white.
- Iterate all these steps again but with the 3rd and 4th color, and the 3rd and 4th noise field respectively.
- Do this second iteration with a HARD_LIGHT blend mode.

The left bar is produced this way. The right bar is produced the same way but 
- with the four colors swapped (1<->3, 2<->4)
- colors slightly modulated in their hues.
- with a blendMode of SOFT_LIGHT instead of HARD_LIGHT

Created by @aschmidt75 in 2022 using p5js.
https://linktr.ee/aschmidt75

metadata.name: Flowers #189
metadata.description:
This project is inspired by natural flowers.
Flowers and foliage in the piece are arranged randomly, but they follow a regular pattern, as flowers do as they grow.
Initially, flowers are produced randomly and without color. Afterwards, the pieces are painted according to the color palettes, so that viewers can feel the effect of colors.
Each piece is processed until the frame part is reached.

Fully generated by p5.js

Press 's' to get a 3000x3000 px PNG file.

metadata.name: blind vision (audio) #73
metadata.description:
- 40 very short stories of real people about being blind

- each one is written in braille (you can see it, but probably don't know how to read) 

- and the same story is recorded as audio, generated by synthetic voice-over (that will help)

- fingerprint on each picture touches braille text (that's how it usually works for braille)

- photos on the background are hardly readable (cause visual beauty is a small percentage of beauty)

- background sounds are manually recorded all over the world 

This media-mix can't be fully understood by both sides - by those who is blind nor by those who is sighted and that's the kind of a point.


*Sound launches by click. Next clicks multiply it.
For iOS - "silent mode" has to be turned off)

code by @tequibo

metadata.name: AI Japanese garden #3
metadata.description:
This artwork is a Digital Collage and Image Compositing

In this Digital Artwork, I have used a combination of CG and artificial intelligence, as well as layers of texture to convey a visual pleasure to the viewer. The random combination of these layers creates an image that is very different from what a human can create.
